Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu meets with U.S. Sen. Lindsey Graham at the Israeli Prime Minister's Office in West Jerusalem on Dec. 21, 2025. (Amos Ben Gershom / GPO / Handout/Anadolu via Getty Images)

Graham's announcement comes less than a month after he met with Netanyahu in [Israel](https://www.foxnews.com/category/world/world-regions/israel) in December.

In a [video](https://x.com/IsraeliPM/status/2002716710420594849) posted to X on December 21, Netanyahu welcomed the senator, calling Graham "a great friend of Israel" and "great personal friend."

